\section{The Comb Page Theorem: Unitarity Restored}
\label{sec:page_theorem}
\subsection{Statement}
Let $s_k \approx \log d_{R_k}$ be the coarse entropy of mode $R_k$.
\begin{theorem}[Comb Page Theorem]
\label{thm:comb-page}
Under P0--P4, with $U_k$ typical scramblers (Haar or $t$-design on $I_{k-1}M_{k-1}$),
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:comb-page}
S(R_{\le n}) = \min\!\left\{\sum_{k=1}^n s_k,\ \ S_{\rm BH}(u_n) + S(I_0, M_0)\right\} \ \pm O\!\big(\log S_{\rm BH}\big).
\end{equation}
If the initial state is pure ($S(I_0, M_0)=0$), $S(R_{\le n})$ rises until the Page time and then decreases with $S(R_{\le n}) \approx S_{\rm BH}(u_n)$.
\end{theorem}

\subsection{Achievability via Decoupling and Approximate Designs}
Decoupling proves that, for typical scramblers, early radiation $R_{\le n}$ is nearly maximally mixed when $d_{R_{\le n}}\ll d_{M_n}$; the joint state of $(M_n I_n)$ retains the coherent information. Post-Page, as $d_{M_n}$ shrinks (P0), the coherent information must flow to $R_{\le n}$ by unitarity. With approximate $t$-designs (local random circuits of polylog depth), deviations are bounded by additive $O(\log S_{\rm BH})$ terms~\cite{Brandao:2016}, which do not change the turnover. The argument mirrors quantum-capacity achievability proofs by hashing/decoupling, now applied \emph{with memory} through the comb.

\subsection{Converse and Finite-Size Corrections}
A converse follows from entropy inequalities and purity: $S(R_{\le n})=S(M_n I_n)$, hence $S(R_{\le n})\le S_{\rm BH}(u_n)+S(I_0,M_0)$. Finite-size corrections arise from (i) imperfect scramblers (finite design order), (ii) finite memory time $\tau_{\rm mem}$, and (iii) non-Gaussian kernel corrections. These contribute subleading $\tilde{O}(\log S_{\rm BH})$ shifts without affecting the turnover or endpoint purity.

\subsection{Numerical Validation}
We validate Eq.~\eqref{eq:comb-page} with toy, exact comb, and MPS/MPO data. All error bars are shown explicitly.

