\section{Predictions and Falsifiability}
\label{sec:predictions}
% (unchanged; now linked to QEC diagnostics narrative)
HMC predicts gentle, retarded sidebands in temporal correlators and thus small but structured quantum error correlations. Analogue experiments and GW ringdown analyses can be equipped with matched filters and model-selection criteria; QEC-inspired diagnostics (e.g., entanglement-fidelity proxies under correlated noise) strengthen interpretability.

\section{Discussion and Outlook}
\label{sec:discussion}
\paragraph{QEC perspective.} The HMC reinterpretation as an OAQEC process with a forgetful memory channel clarifies diary-recovery, coherent information flow, and robustness to correlated errors. It bridges HMC to holographic QEC insights while remaining dynamical and applicable beyond AdS.

